abstract: Mr. Kent, a senior State Department official, appeared on Capitol Hill for testimony Wednesday as the public impeachment hearings began.
snippet: Mr. Kent, a senior State Department official, appeared on Capitol Hill for testimony Wednesday as the public impeachment hearings began.
lead_paragraph: George P. Kent, a senior State Department official, appeared on Capitol Hill for testimony Wednesday during public hearings as lawmakers consider whether to impeach President Trump for what Democrats say was an effort to use the power of his office for political gain.

abstract: Who is John Solomon? His name popped up frequently in closed-door testimony in the impeachment query. He is a regular on Hannity. And his work helps shape how millions of Americans understand this moment.
snippet: Who is John Solomon? His name popped up frequently in closed-door testimony in the impeachment query. He is a regular on Hannity. And his work helps shape how millions of Americans understand this moment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In weeks of closed-door testimony, American officials who worked in Ukraine kept circling back to the work of one journalist, John Solomon, whose articles they said appeared to have considerable currency with President Trump’s inner circle.

headline_main: The Man Trump Trusts for News on Ukraine
headline_print_headline: Fox News Face  And Key Figure In Investigation
byline_original: By Jeremy W. Peters and Kenneth P. Vogel

abstract: The president’s efforts to prevent the House from doing its job are just as worrisome as the Ukraine scandal.
snippet: The president’s efforts to prevent the House from doing its job are just as worrisome as the Ukraine scandal.
lead_paragraph: The public impeachment hearings this week will be at least as important for what is not said as for what is. Congress will no doubt focus a lot on President Trump’s dealings with Ukraine and his secret plan to get that government to announce a public investigation of the man he considered his chief political rival, Joe Biden.

abstract: From denials of a quid pro quo to attacks on impeachment inquiry witnesses, here’s a look at some of the arguments made by the president and his supporters.
snippet: From denials of a quid pro quo to attacks on impeachment inquiry witnesses, here’s a look at some of the arguments made by the president and his supporters.
lead_paragraph: President Trump and his supporters have tried out a variety of talking points defending his attempts to press the Ukrainian government to open investigations that would benefit him politically.

headline_main: Assessing the Impeachment Defenses Offered by Trump and His Allies

abstract: The public phase of the House impeachment inquiry into President Trump begins Wednesday. Here’s how it will unfold.
snippet: The public phase of the House impeachment inquiry into President Trump begins Wednesday. Here’s how it will unfold.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats will convene open presidential impeachment hearings on Wednesday for only the third time in modern United States history, calling senior American diplomats to testify about President Trump’s attempts to pressure a foreign power to publicly commit to investigate his political rivals.

abstract: The president blames Michael Atkinson, whom he appointed, for finding the anonymous whistle-blower’s complaint on his interactions with Ukraine to be credible.
snippet: The president blames Michael Atkinson, whom he appointed, for finding the anonymous whistle-blower’s complaint on his interactions with Ukraine to be credible.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has discussed dismissing the intelligence community’s inspector general, Michael Atkinson, because Mr. Atkinson reported a whistle-blower’s complaint about Mr. Trump’s interactions with Ukraine to Congress after concluding it was credible, according to four people familiar with the discussions.

abstract: Quite a few people, and they have something in common. It’s not poverty.
snippet: Quite a few people, and they have something in common. It’s not poverty.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has been good for America’s billionaires. He slashed corporate taxes, cut the top income tax rate and raised the total exemption for the estate tax, directly benefiting several hundred billionaires and their heirs. He’s placed wealthy supporters in key positions of government like the Commerce Department, rolled back Obama-era financial regulations and privileged the interests of favored industries — like resource extraction and fossil fuel production — above all else.
